The Minnesota Department of Education (MDE) is working closely with the Minnesota Department of Health as they plan for the 2020-21 school year, and they want parents and families to share their distance learning experiences by taking this Fall Planning Survey.

This feedback is extremely valuable, will help inform the department about balancing work and family responsibilities while also supporting student learners.

The survey is available in English, Hmong, Somali, and Spanish, and will close on June 30, 2020.

Please share widely with your friends, family, communities, and social networks.

Paper enrollment: we have group enrollment forms {great for classroom signups or ECFE-type of settings}, along with individual signup sheets in English, Spanish and Somali {these are great for one-on-one interactions with parents, or ‚Äònew family packets.‚Äô

post_text:
Storing and managing digital photos is vitally important as most of us don't have physical copies of these items, and once lost, these files are gone forever. In this class we will discuss the best practices to store digital photos, how to move them, back them up and manage them within a computer, smartphone or tablet. The focus of this class will be on iPhone and Android devices, but will touch on both Macs and Windows PCs as well. We will discuss the benefits and drawbacks of using "cloud" storage services like Apple's iCloud and Google Photos.

When: Monday, October 21 from 5 - 7pm
Where: McGregor High School Business Lab
Instructor: Joe Simenstad
Fee: $30
Register: lkruse@isd4.org or 218.768.5133

Wow! What a day! Thank you to Jay and Erik for an awesome adventure on the farm! BSWI environmentalist's discovered all about life on the organic farm! They planted, turned up soil, pulled weeds, played with farm animals, gathered and graded eggs, went on a hay ride, made gourd bird houses, had a lettuce taste test, and so much more! A shout out to our farmer friends who shared their love of horticulture and life on the farm!

shared_text:
McGregor Community Education added 22 new photos ‚Äî in East Lake, Minnesota.
July 11, 2019 at 12:53 PM ¬∑ East Lake, MN ¬∑

Several animals call Rice Lake National Wildlife Refuge home...like a beaver! Ever wonder why a beaver has that big flat tail? Students interacted through games to learn about the special features animals have and how their activities, behaviors, and body parts help them to survive. Students fine tuned their observation skills on a short nature hike and did some journaling along the way. One of the favorites for students is time at Rice River fishing! A huge thanks to Walt Ford, Manager and the fishing volunteers who made the day so memorable!

shared_text:
McGregor Community Education added 19 new photos.
July 11, 2019 at 12:44 PM ¬∑

I have not met one kid that does not enjoy kayaking! Expert kayakers Mr. and Mrs. Hadrich teach BSWI students all about safety, technique, paddling and navigating the waters all while having fun! So much fun that some choose to end the session tipping in the kayak...on purpose!
While the first kayak session was impacted by a thunderstorm it did not stop the action! Students were inside learning about pollinators within our ecosystem and interactive games learning about prey and predator relationships.
Have you ever eaten dandelion bread? Our youngest learners tasted it first hand and it was DELICIOUS! Thank you Courtney Kinnett for the wonderful sampling! Prior to the sampling students learned all about edible foods in the forest with an engaging Foe or Friend activity that Lucas the Park Ranger took them through. What a great day of learning!
